decision_conditions:
FORMAL DECISION:  For the above reasons the Planning Inspectorate hereby allow the appeal and grant planning permission for demolition of the existing building, retention of front wall and redevelopment to provide six number one-bed flats, at the Whittington and Cat Public House, 89 Highgate Hill, Islington, London, N19 in accordance with the terms of the application reference P041269 dated 23rd May 2004 and the plans submitted therewith, subject to the following conditions:

1.  the development hereby permitted shall be begun before the expiration of five years from the date of this decision;

2.  with the exception of rainwater pipes, no plumbing or pipes shall be fixed to the external face of the development hereby permitted;

3.  before the development hereby permitted is commenced, details of the materials to be used for external finishes shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details;

4.  before the development hereby permitted is commenced, details of a scheme for the stabilisation and retention of the existing facade of the building at the site and for its tying back to the new structure, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details;

5.  before the development hereby permitted is commenced, details of a scheme for the provision of sound insulation between the residential units hereby approved shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details, with the soundproofing measures thus installed thereafter permanently retained.
